Concept:     Transfer Learning
Category:    Technique
Definition:  Reuses pre-trained model weights for new related tasks
Year:        2009
Researchers: Pan and Yang survey
Applications:Fine-tuning LLMs, computer vision
Related:     Pre-training, fine-tuning, domain adaptation

Concept:     Attention Mechanism
Category:    Mechanism
Definition:  Learns to focus on relevant input parts for each output
Year:        2015
Researchers: Bahdanau et al.
Applications:Machine translation, NLP, summarization
Related:     Self-attention, multi-head, cross-attention

Concept:     Backpropagation
Category:    Training
Definition:  Computes gradients via chain rule through network layers
Year:        1986
Researchers: Rumelhart/Hinton
Applications:Training all neural networks
Related:     Gradient descent, automatic differentiation

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is a programming language?
A1: A programming language is a formal set of instructions
     for computers. High-level languages (Python, Java) are
     human-readable; low-level (Assembly) are closer to
     machine code.

Q2: What is democracy?
A2: Democracy is government where power derives from the
     people through free elections, rule of law, and
     protection of minority rights. Types include direct and
     representative democracy.

Q3: What is the Renaissance?
A3: The Renaissance (14th-17th century) was a cultural
     rebirth in Europe featuring renewed interest in Greco-
     Roman art, humanism, and early science. Began in Italy;
     spread across Europe.

Q4: What is photosynthesis?
A4: Photosynthesis converts sunlight, CO2, and water into
     glucose and oxygen: 6CO2 + 6H2O + light → C6H12O6 +
     6O2. It occurs in plant chloroplasts.

Q5: What is the speed of light?
A5: The speed of light in a vacuum is 299,792,458 meters
     per second (approximately 300,000 km/s), denoted as c.

